4. Differentiate between ArrayList and LinkedList?
-->
    | ArrayList                         | LinkedList                |
    | --------------------------------- | ------------------------- |
    | Uses Dynamic Array                | Uses Doubly Linked List   |
    | Fast random access                | Slow random access        |
    | Slow insertion/deletion in middle | Fast insertion/deletion   |
    | Less memory                       | More memory               |
    | Implements List                   | Implements List and Deque |
    
    Complexity :
      | Operation      | ArrayList | LinkedList                 |
      | -------------- | --------- | -------------------------- |
      | get()          | O(1)      | O(n)                       |
      | add(end)       | O(1)      | O(1)                       |
      | insert(middle) | O(n)      | O(1) (after reaching node) |
      | remove(middle) | O(n)      | O(1) (after reaching node) |
    
    Interview Tip :
        More searching → ArrayList
        More insert/delete → LinkedList




5. Differentiate between Comparable and Comparator?
-->
| Comparable           | Comparator              |
| -------------------- | ----------------------- |
| Interface            | Interface               |
| Package: `java.lang` | Package: `java.util`    |
| Natural ordering     | Custom ordering         |
| `compareTo()` method | `compare()` method      |
| One sorting logic    | Multiple sorting logics |
 

Comparable :
    class Student implements Comparable<Student>{
    
        public int compareTo(Student s){
            return this.id - s.id;
        }
    }
Comparator :
    Comparator<Student> byName =
    (a,b) -> a.name.compareTo(b.name);
    Interview Tip
    Comparable → Natural Sorting
    Comparator → Custom Sorting



