15. Differentiate between Iterator and ListIterator?
-->
| Iterator                       | ListIterator                                         |
| ------------------------------ | ---------------------------------------------------- |
| Works with all collections     | Works only with List implementations                 |
| Forward traversal only         | Forward and backward traversal                       |
| Can remove elements            | Can add, remove, and replace elements                |
| Methods: `hasNext()`, `next()` | Adds `hasPrevious()`, `previous()`, `add()`, `set()` |
| Obtained using `iterator()`    | Obtained using `listIterator()`                      |

    Iterator Example :
        Iterator<String> it = list.iterator();
        while(it.hasNext()){
            System.out.println(it.next());
        }
    
    ListIterator Example :
        ListIterator<String> it = list.listIterator();
        
        while(it.hasNext()){
            System.out.println(it.next());
        }
        
        while(it.hasPrevious()){
            System.out.println(it.previous());
        }



Interview Tip :
      Iterator → One-way traversal
      ListIterator → Two-way traversal (Lists only)






16. Differentiate between HashSet and TreeSet?
-->
| HashSet                 | TreeSet                                |
| ----------------------- | -------------------------------------- |
| Unordered               | Sorted                                 |
| Uses Hash Table         | Uses Red-Black Tree                    |
| Faster (`O(1)` average) | Slower (`O(log n)`)                    |
| Allows one null         | Does not allow null (natural ordering) |
