        [20, 10, 30]
    
    TreeSet :
        TreeSet<Integer> set = new TreeSet<>();
        set.add(30);
        set.add(10);
        set.add(20);
        System.out.println(set);
    
    Output :
        [10, 20, 30]


Interview Tip :
    HashSet → Fast lookups
    TreeSet → Sorted elements




17. Differentiate between Queue and Deque?
-->
| Queue                     | Deque                           |
| ------------------------- | ------------------------------- |
| FIFO (First In First Out) | Double-ended queue              |
| Insert at rear            | Insert at both front and rear   |
| Remove from front         | Remove from both front and rear |
| Limited operations        | More flexible operations        |
| Interface: Queue          | Interface: Deque                |

    Queue Example :
        Queue<Integer> queue = new LinkedList<>();
        queue.offer(10);
        queue.offer(20);
        System.out.println(queue.poll());
    
    Output :
    10
    
    Deque Example :
        Deque<Integer> deque = new ArrayDeque<>();
        deque.addFirst(10);
        deque.addLast(20);
        System.out.println(deque);
    
    Output :
        [10, 20]
    
    Interview Tip :
        Queue → One end for insertion, one end for deletion
        Deque → Both ends for insertion and deletion



